private TreeNode<T> rotateRight(TreeNode<T> node){
    if(node == null || node.getLeft() == null) return node; // Check for null nodes
    TreeNode<T> left = node.getLeft(); // Get the left child of the current node
    node.setLeft(left.getRight()); // Set the left child's right child as the current node's left child
    left.setRight(node); // Set the current node as the right child of the left child
    updateHeightAndSubtreeSize(node); // Update the heights and subtree sizes of the rotated nodes
    updateHeightAndSubtreeSize(left); // Update the heights and subtree sizes of the rotated nodes
    return left; // Return the new root of the rotated subtree
}
